omic modeling, statistics, and econometrics. It covers the basic results of the theory as well as their relations to linear programming, network flow problems, convex analysis, and computational geometry. Emphasizing computational methods, it also includes programming examples that provide details on implementation. Applications include discrete choice models, models of differential demand, and quantile-based statistical estimation methods, as well as asset pricing models.Authoritative and accessible, Optimal Transport Methods in Economics also features numerous exercises throughout that help you develop your mathematical agility, deepen your computational skills, and strengthen your economic intuition.The first introduction to the subject written especially for economistsIncludes programming examplesFeatures numerous exercises throughoutIdeal for students and researchers alike  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEconomicsxMathematical models. 0aEconomics, Mathematical. 0aEconomics; Mathematical models. 0aMathematical optimization. 0aTransportation problems (Programming). 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / Microeconomics.2bisacsh  aMonge problem.  aMongeЋantorovich problem.  aapplied economics.  acomputation.  acomputational geometry.  aconvex analysis.  adual minimizers.  adual problem.  aduality.  aeconometrics.  aeconomic modeling.  aeconomic output.  aeconomics.  aequilibrium transport.  ageneralized convexity.  ahedonic equilibria.  ainversion demand.  alinear programming.  amarginal probability distributions.  amatching surplus.  anetwork flow problems.  aoptimal assignment.  aoptimal network flow.  aoptimal transport theory.  aoptimal transport.  apolar factorization theorem.  apositive assortative matching.  aprimal problem.  aquantile regressio